sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K106674
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
8xLexA operator-Cyc1P-GFP-Adh1t
A targeted (LexA Operators) silencing. Contained in the yeast pRS315 integration vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jacinto Chen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K106673
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
8xLexA Operators-Cyc1p.
A PspomI site on the outside of 8xLexA operators and a broken PspomI site in between the LexA ops and Cyc1P.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jacinto Chen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: A scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Scar site created by A part ligation. Used for entering composite parts on the Registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Horwitz

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K106671
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of a yeast optimized GFP with BD ends for AarI cloning.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jacinto Chen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: PCR amplified from lab plasmid stocks.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: As an AD part, there is no ATG, and the stop codon is included. For more information on AarI cloning, please refer to the UCSF 2008 igem page.
